A vintage 1960s spy thriller movie poster style illustration showing a massive Art Deco bank vault door partially open, with golden light spilling out from within, revealing stacked rows of sealed envelopes and documents behind steel bars. In the foreground, a shadowy figure in a fedora peers around a corner, while another silhouette of a security guard with a ring of oversized keys stands vigilant. The scene uses rich amber, deep burgundy, and noir-inspired shadows, with dramatic diagonal lighting reminiscent of classic heist films. The vault mechanism displays intricate gears and multiple combination locks layered upon each other, suggesting layers of protection. Dust particles float in the golden beam of light, adding atmosphere and tension to the scene.
